    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="figure" subtype="drawing">
                <figure>
                    <head type="title"><title type="artwork" corresp="#JRLILLESTREETMSIX">Vignette, Lille Street with Wagon</title></head>
                    <figDesc>Pen and ink, approx. ? &#x00D7; ? cm (image only).</figDesc>
                    <p>The editors of the <ref type="note" subtype="bibliographical" target="library_edition_note.php">Library Edition</ref> 
                        describe the image as a &#x201C;sketch of a street, with waggon and horses in the foreground&#x201D; 
                        (<ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#JRWORKSLE">Ruskin, <hi rend="italic">Works</hi></ref>, 2:344 n. 2). 
                        The vignette is drawn in the manner of <ref type="note" subtype="biographical" target="prout_samuel_note.php">Samuel Prout (<date when="1783">1783</date>&#x2013;<date when="1852">1852</date>)</ref>, 
                        suggesting without specifically copying <title type="artwork" corresp="#PROUTGHENT">&#x201C;Ghent&#x201D;</title> 
                        in <ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#PROUTSKETCHES"><title type="artwork" corresp="#PROUTSKETCHES"><hi rend="italic">Facsimiles of Sketches Made in Flanders and Germany</hi></title> (<date when="1833">1833</date>)</ref>, 
                        but at a considerably reduced scale.</p>
                    <p><persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName> is believed to have made a tour sketch of a subject in <placeName corresp="#LILLE">Lille</placeName>, 
                        but the location of the sketch is unknown; see <ref type="note" subtype="contextual" target="drawings_1833_note.php">Drawings from the <date notBefore="1833-05-14" notAfter="1833-08-19">Tour of 1833</date></ref>.</p>
                </figure>
            </div>
